The Edo State Government has announced that schools across the state are to resume on Wednesday, February 20, for the continuation of the second term academic session, after the mid-term break. In a statement signed by the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Education, Dr. Mrs. R. E. Obahiagbon, the government said that the mid-term break for 2nd Term ends Tuesday, 19 February 2019. According to her, “This is to inform the general public that the mid-term break for 2nd term (2018/2019 academic session) ends today, Tuesday, 19 February, 2019. Schools are expected to resume tomorrow Wednesday, 20 February, 2019 “All schools are by this announcement advised to comply accordingly.”